On the basis of the information provided by Member States, the Director-General of UNESCO presents a biennial Report on the Safety of Journalists and the Danger of Impunity to the Intergovernmental Council of the International Programme for the Development of Communication (IPDC). Every other year, a chapter on the safety of journlaists is included in the World Trends in Freedom of Expression and Media Development Report.

SOURCEDETAIL: The figures included here concern only cases of killing of journalists and associated media personnel. UNESCO does not collect data on trade unionists and human rights advocates, nor does it collect data on the number of cases of kidnapping, enforced disappearance, arbitrary detention or torture of journalists and associated media personnel.
